Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}. Core and finely chop @Roma Tomato{1}(finely chopped). Remove and discard tough stems and ribs from @Kale{4}; roughly chop leaves. Chop @Garlic Clove{2}(minced). Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12} into 1-inch cubes and place in a #medium pot{} with enough water to cover by 2 inches.

Bring potatoes to a boil. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup cooking water, then drain and return to #pot{}. Mash to desired consistency with a #potato masher{}. Stir in @Parmesan Cheese{¼}, @Sour Cream{4}, and @Butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cover pot and set aside.

> TIP: If needed, add cooking water 1-2 TBSP at a time to create a creamy consistency.

Meanwhile, heat another @Butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat (we used nonstick). Add onion, @Sugar{½%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, tossing occasionally, until softened, about ~{10%minutes}. Increase heat to medium high. Stir in tomato, @Balsamic Vinegar{5}, and ⅓ cup tap water. Cook until jammy, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper; set aside.

While onion cooks, pat @Chicken Fillet{12} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with plenty of salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink in center, about ~{6-8%minutes} per side. Transfer to pan with onion jam. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Place kale and 1 TBSP tap water in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave on high until tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Carefully remove wrap. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in large pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Toss in kale and any liquid in bowl. Cook until liquid evaporates, about ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season kale with salt and pepper. Divide mashed potatoes, kale, and chicken between plates. Spoon onion jam over chicken and serve.